              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2190251608232043959">The start of a well-known series. While the writing was on par with many fantasies I&apos;ve read, the characters and setting did not amaze me. It is dragon-centric, so heavy with dragon-lore and dragon-activities and dragon-relationships and dragony stuff that it left me curious about the characters.<br/><br/>For all of its world building, threads and mind-tapping, and so forth, it fell rather flat for me. I can see how plenty of people will enjoy the series. It has the right tropes, and it is competently wri</span>
  <span id="freeText2190251608232043959" style="display:none">The start of a well-known series. While the writing was on par with many fantasies I've read, the characters and setting did not amaze me. It is dragon-centric, so heavy with dragon-lore and dragon-activities and dragon-relationships and dragony stuff that it left me curious about the characters.<br /><br />For all of its world building, threads and mind-tapping, and so forth, it fell rather flat for me. I can see how plenty of people will enjoy the series. It has the right tropes, and it is competently written, but the power and majesty of the author's fictional universe did not come through. While reading more compelling series at the moment, I was less than impressed by this one.</span>
